{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1492605273,"nonce":"Reskk7+/eh6Pt3CTE3Dpvgip6j0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMjI3MjI5OTc=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1262","origin":"github"},"title":"Declaring packages legacy and marking them as unmaintained","message":"Dear @galaxyproject/iuc \n\nI would like to move all packages on the IUC's github repo into the deprecated folder, so that it is clear that the way forward is to abandon these packages. The infrastructure for using Conda is in place in galaxy since 16.01, and I would consider this mature since 17.01.\n\nThis may be a problem for administrators running older galaxy versions, but the likelihood of successfully installing things like R or deeptools with the complete dependency chain from scratch today is low (outdated download links, newer/older gcc versions, etc. pp.).\nI personally consider time spent on toolshed packages in 2017 a waste of time (on top of it being a frustrating experience).\n\nConsequently, I think we should also lobby for toolshed package dependency installations to not be the default, starting as soon as possible.","files":null}]}